                                "stop": 8.801,
                                "byte_start": 107520,
                                "byte_stop": 142733,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has the opinion of the Court in case 07-543, AT\u0026T Corporation versus Hulteen."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.801,
                        "stop": 204.528,
                        "byte_start": 142733,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.801,
                                "stop": 14.82,
                                "byte_start": 142733,
                                "byte_stop": 166870,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.82,
                                "stop": 19.987,
                                "byte_start": 166870,
                                "byte_stop": 187559,
                                "text": "AT\u0026T provides pensions and other benefits based on a seniority system."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.987,
                                "stop": 28.494,
                                "byte_start": 187559,
                                "byte_stop": 221518,
                                "text": "The system relies on an employee\u0027s term of employment which is understood as the period of service to the company minus uncredited leave time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.494,
                                "stop": 42.772,
                                "byte_start": 221518,
                                "byte_stop": 278674,
                                "text": "In the 1960s and early to mid 1970s, AT\u0026T gave full service credit to employees on disability leave, but did not treat pregnancy-related absence as equivalent to disability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.772,
                                "stop": 52.508,
                                "byte_start": 278674,
                                "byte_stop": 317649,
                                "text": "Women including Noreen Hulteen therefore received less service credit for pregnancy leave than they would have accrued on the same leave for disability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.508,
                                "stop": 56.867,
                                "byte_start": 317649,
                                "byte_stop": 334994,
                                "text": "At that time, AT\u0026T\u0027s differential leave policy was lawful."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.867,
                                "stop": 70.793,
                                "byte_start": 334994,
                                "byte_stop": 390792,
                                "text": "This Court in the case of General Electric Company against Gilbert concluded that a disability plan excluding disabilities related to pregnancy was not sex-based discrimination within the meaning of Title VII."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.793,
                                "stop": 89.153,
                                "byte_start": 390792,
                                "byte_stop": 464144,
                                "text": "In 1979, in response to Gilbert, Congress passed the Pregnancy Discrimination Act or PDA which amended Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 and defined sex-based discrimination to include discrimination because of or on the basis of pregnancy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.153,
                                "stop": 101.24,
                                "byte_start": 464144,
                                "byte_stop": 512522,
                                "text": "In light of the change in the law, AT\u0026T promptly changed its policy and provided service credit for pregnancy leave on the same basis as leave taken for other temporary disabilities."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.24,
                                "stop": 111.363,
                                "byte_start": 512522,
                                "byte_stop": 553064,
                                "text": "AT\u0026T did not however, make any retroactive adjustments to the service credit calculations of women who had been subject to the pre-PDA policies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.363,
                                "stop": 122.941,
                                "byte_start": 553064,
                                "byte_stop": 599353,
                                "text": "Hulteen has now retired and if her total term of employment had not been decreased due to her pre-PDA pregnancy leave, she would be entitled to a greater pension benefit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.941,
                                "stop": 131.762,
                                "byte_start": 599353,
                                "byte_stop": 634671,
                                "text": "She sued AT\u0026T seeking increased benefits alleging discrimination on the basis of sex and pregnancy in violation of Title VII."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.762,
                                "stop": 137.61,
                                "byte_start": 634671,
                                "byte_stop": 657972,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit found such a violation but we now reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.61,
                                "stop": 148.762,
                                "byte_start": 657972,
                                "byte_stop": 702589,
                                "text": "Section 703(h) of Title VII expressly protects the application of different standards of compensation under the terms of a bona fide seniority system."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.762,
                                "stop": 157.405,
                                "byte_start": 702589,
                                "byte_stop": 737176,
                                "text": "In other words, it insulates from challenge seniority systems producing differences that are not the result of an intention to discriminate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.405,
                                "stop": 170.855,
                                "byte_start": 737176,
                                "byte_stop": 790988,
                                "text": "Hulteen argues that AT\u0026T\u0027s differential leave policy was discriminatory and that the policy infects the seniority system making the differences, it generates the different pension pay outs, open the challenge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.855,
                                "stop": 186.694,
                                "byte_start": 790988,
                                "byte_stop": 854309,
                                "text": "But in light of this Court\u0027s decision in Gilbert, the fact that the -- and the fact that the PDA is not retroactive, AT\u0026T\u0027s differential leave policy cannot be considered as illegal when done and therefore, cannot be termed intentionally discriminatory."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.694,
                                "stop": 196.335,
                                "byte_start": 854309,
                                "byte_stop": 892865,
                                "text": "AT\u0026T\u0027s seniority system is therefore a bona fide system under Section 703(h) and is insulated from challenge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.335,
                                "stop": 199.301,
                                "byte_start": 892865,
                                "byte_stop": 904777,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.301,
                                "stop": 204.528,
                                "byte_start": 904777,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Breyer joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
